	h1	IDEs

	p	Tools to help you develop Fantom code.



	h2	F4

	p	F4 by Xored is a fully featured eclipse based IDE, including a debugger - written in Fantom!
	
	a.noIcon (href="https://github.com/xored/f4/releases")
		img.rounded.img-fluid.float-left.mr-3 (src="data:image/png;base64,")

	== app.renderLinkBy("F4 IDE v1.1.2", "https://github.com/xored/f4/releases", "Xored Software, Inc.", null)

	p	F4 comes bundled with its own embedded Fantom 1.0.71 runtime, so does not require Fantom to be installed on your system.

	p	F4 is tailered towards developing Fantom pods and projects, as oppose to individual script files. See the following for details: 

	== app.renderLinkOn("An Introduction to the F4 IDE - Video Tutorial", "http://www.alienfactory.co.uk/articles/intro-to-f4", "Alien-Factory", null)
	
	p	The source code for F4 may be found on the <a href="https://github.com/xored/f4">GitHub F4 IDE</a> project page.

	p	Plugins for F4:

	ul.list-unstyled
		li;	== app.renderLinkBy("FPM", "https://bitbucket.org/AlienFactory/f4-features/", "Steve Eynon", "Provides different pod versions from multiple repositories to F4 projects.")

	ul.list-unstyled
		li;	== app.renderLinkBy("TrioEditor", "https://gitlab.com/NeedleInAJayStack/trioeditor/tree/master", "Jay Herron", "Trio file editor and Axon syntax highlighter for SkySpark projects.")



	h2	Fantom Online
	
	p	Program and run Fantom code online, without installing anything!
	
	== app.renderLinkOn("Coding Ground", "http://www.tutorialspoint.com/execute_fantom_online.php", "Tutorials Point (Fantom 1.0.66)", null)

	p	Use Coding Ground's virtual file system and command prompt to create and run Fantom mini-projects. 
	
	== app.renderLinkBy("Ideone", "http://ideone.com/fork/BVOZYC/", "Sphere Engine (Fantom 1.0.67)", null)

	p	Use Ideone to easily fork, run, and share Fantom samples.



	h2	Camebert

	p	Camebert is a lightweight, SWT based IDE that may be used for multiple programming languages, including Fantom.
	
	== app.renderLinkBy("Camebert IDE", "http://www.status302.com/camembert#.V2LYWxZuEgQ", "Thibaut Colar", null)

	p	Camebert itself is written in Fantom.


		
	h2	JetBrains - Intelli-J IDEA
	
	p	JetBrains haven't produced an IDE for Fantom yet, but if you'd like them to, then lobby this issue here:

	== app.renderLinkOn("Request for Fantom Support", "https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-177055", "JetBrains YouTrack", null)

	p	Note you must first be signed up to JetBrain's YouTrack to be eligible to vote - a 30 second process!
	
	
	
	h2	Visual Studio Code
	
	p	Visual Studio Code is a source-code editor developed by Microsoft for Windows, Linux and macOS. It includes support for debugging, embedded Git control and GitHub, syntax highlighting, intelligent code completion, snippets, and code refactoring.

	== app.renderLinkOn("Visual Studio Code", "https://code.visualstudio.com/download", "by Microsoft", null)
	
	p	There is an extension available for Fantom called "Fantom Syntax Highlighting", which can be downloaded in the IDE via the extensions tab.
	
	

